How to use RT :

First five lines are mandatory.
Camera orientation is expressed in degres.
Intensity applies to all lights and must be comprised between 0 and 1.
All shape normals must be comprised between -1 and 1. If normal values are incoherent, render is undefined.
Ambient light must be set on line 6.
Shape colors (r, g, b) must be comprised between 0 and 1.
If shape height is set to 0, shape will be infinite.
Shape radius must be above 0.
Number of lights and shapes are not limited.

scene_name=[name]
camera=[posX, posY, posZ, orientationX, orientationY, orientationZ]
intensity=[value]
shadow=[yes/no]
shine=[yes/no]
ambient_light=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, r, g, b]
light=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, r, g, b]
plane=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, r, g, b]
sphere=[posX, posY, posZ, radius, r, g, b]
cylinder=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, radius, height, r, g, b]
cone=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, radius, height, r, g, b]
hyperboloid=[posX, posY, posZ, normalX, normalY, normalZ, radius, r, g, b]

Left clic to select to shape you want to modify, right clic to unselect.

Keys :
-Enter RT: space
-Exit RT: esc
-Remove form: delete
-Change mode (edit / diffuse / reflection): L
-Move camera:
	rotation: arrows + n + m
	position: w / s / a / d / z / x
-Move shape:
	rotation: use interface or 7 / 8 / 4 / 5 / 1 / 2
	position: t / g / f / h / scroll mouse
	radius: + / -
-Export:
	file: c
	image: return
-Lights:
	select light: 1 / 2
	to move lights use same keys as shapes
-Options:
	antialiasing: u
	reflection coeficient: r

